  </i>
  453 U.S. 322, 329-334, 101 S.Ct. 2789, 2794-2796, 69 L.Ed.2d 672 (1981) (Congress intended that union welfare funds regulated by the Taft-Hartley Act, see 29 U.S.C. § 186(c)(5), be operated under traditional trust law principles, and this desire became explicit in ERISA).
